# Persisted context (hyperhdr-ha)

## Project overview

Home Assistant custom component for **HyperHDR** ambient lighting. Repo: `mjoshd/hyperhdr-ha`. Manifest version: `0.1.6`. Config entry version: `2`. Dependency: `hyperhdr-py-sickkick==0.2.0`.

## Platforms & entities

| Platform | Entities |
|----------|----------|
| `camera` | LED Colors (`HyperHDRLedCamera`), LED Gradient (`HyperHDRLedGradientCamera`) â€” WebSocket streams via `hyperhdr.stream`, disabled by default |
| `light` | Light, Priority Light |
| `sensor` | Visible Priority, Average Color (throttled 2s, deduped) |
| `switch` | Component switches (All, Smoothing, Blackbar Detection, HDR, LED Device, etc.) â€” disabled by default; only created for components the server reports (avoids `componentstate` validation errors on legacy IDs) |
| `number` | Smoothing Time / Decay / Update Freq only â€” **only if** `hyperhdr_client.smoothing is not None` (HDR tone mapping number entity removed from setup; class may remain for registry cleanup) |
| `select` | Smoothing Type â€” **only if** smoothing data exists |

## Key architecture decisions

- **Admin password auth**: When `admin_password` is configured, token is set to `None` for stream constructors. Token login doesn't grant admin privileges needed for `imagestream-start`.
- **Conditional entity creation**: Smoothing entities only created if `hyperhdr_client.smoothing is not None`.
- **Origin strings**: HyperHDR JSON schema limits `origin` to **20 characters** (`HYPERHDR_ORIGIN_MAX_LENGTH = 20`). `sanitize_hyperhdr_origin()` in `const.py`; `DEFAULT_ORIGIN` is built through it. Use for any future user-configurable origin.
- **Brightness (HyperHDR 22+)**: When adjustment has no `brightness`, map HA brightness to **`luminanceGain`**; read-back uses `luminanceGain` when no brightness field.
- **Stale entity cleanup**: `_async_cleanup_stale_entities()` in `__init__.py` removes old camera, color engine, and unsupported smoothing entities from the HA entity registry on every load.
- **Config entry migration**: `async_migrate_entry()` handles v1â†’v2 (no data changes, just version bump).
- **Options flow connection fields**: `HyperHDROptionsFlow` (`config_flow.py`) writes **`CONF_HOST`**, **`CONF_PORT`** (JSON API), **`CONF_PORT_WS`**, and **`CONF_ADMIN_PASSWORD`** into `config_entry.data` (not only options) so cameras and API clients see updates. On save, validates with `raw_connection=True`, requires **`async_sysinfo_id()`** to match **`config_entry.unique_id`** when set (`wrong_device` if another server); `cannot_connect` / `no_id` on failure. Updates entry **`title`** to `host:port`. Strings: `options.step.init.data` (host/port labels) and `options.error` (`cannot_connect`, `no_id`, `wrong_device`) in translations.
- **Camera streaming state**: `_attr_is_streaming` set to `True` on first frame, set back to `False` in `finally` block when frame loop exits.
- **Average color dispatch**: LED Gradient camera computes avg RGB from raw LED data, dispatched via `SIGNAL_AVERAGE_COLOR`, throttled to 2s intervals.
- **Icons**: Defined in `icons.json` (not in translation files â€” hassfest rejects icon keys in translations).

## SSDP discovery

HyperHDR broadcasts `urn:hyperhdr.eu:device:basic:1` as its SSDP service type (from `SSDPHandler.cpp`). Manufacturer: `HyperHDR Open Source Ambient Lighting`. The `async_step_ssdp` in `config_flow.py` extracts host, JSON port (`upnp.ports.jsonServer`), and WebSocket port (from `ssdp_location` URL port). Custom SSDP headers: `HYPERHDR-FBS-PORT`, `HYPERHDR-JSS-PORT`, `HYPERHDR-NAME`.

## Manifest rules

- Keys must be sorted: `domain`, `name`, then **alphabetical** (hassfest enforces this).
- `homeassistant` key is **not allowed** for custom components (only core integrations). Min HA version goes in `hacs.json` only.

## CI / Workflows

Single `.github/workflows/validate.yaml` with two parallel jobs: `hassfest` and `hacs`. Uses `actions/checkout@v4`, `home-assistant/actions/hassfest@master`, `hacs/action@main`. Has `permissions: {}` and `workflow_dispatch`.

## Git / GitHub conventions

- Default branch: `master`
- **Co-authored-by trailers**: Cursor automatically appends `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` to commits. This must be stripped before pushing to avoid "cursoragent" appearing as a GitHub contributor. Use `git filter-branch --msg-filter 'sed "/^Co-authored-by: Cursor/d"'` on affected commits, then force push.
- `.DS_Store` files are gitignored and removed from tracking.

