## Known issues

- **LED Colors stream**: Recurring `Received fragmented control frame` WebSocket error every ~30s causing reconnect cycles. LED Gradient stream is stable.
- **`calculate-colors` command**: Only supported on HyperHDR v20+. Older servers return validation error. `_check_version_supports_calc()` in `sensor.py` prevents sending on unsupported versions.

## hyperhdr-py API surface vs HyperHDR web UI (not in this integration)

These are **runtime + diagnostic** only unless noted. **`hyperhdr-py-sickkick`** does not expose full **config get/set** for instance hardware/effects; constants like `KEY_WLED` exist in the library but **no client methods** use them.

| Topic | In HA today | Notes |
|-------|-------------|--------|
| **Performance** (CPU/RAM/temp, grabber FPS/latency, instance FPS) | No | Library has `benchmark` / `KEY_PERFORMANCE` constants, not live dashboard streams. Would need WebSocket command + payload discovery, then `add_callbacks`. |
| **Effects** (boot effect, background effect, sound device / music viz) | No | Persisted **instance config**; use HyperHDR UI or custom JSON-RPC to `config`-style commands + `saveDB`. |
| **LED Hardware / WLED** (controller type, host IP, RGB order, refresh, override WLED brightness, retries, restore state) | No | Same: **stored configuration**. **LED Device** switch here is only **component enable/disable** for the LED output path, not WLED field editing. |
| **Diagnostics** (`sysinfo`) | Yes (static sensors) | CPU model, hostname, version, etc. â€” **not** live Performance panel metrics. |

